  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>singine-pg</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo class="source">Singine Platform</refmiscinfo>
    <refmiscinfo class="manual">Singine User Commands</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>singine-pg</refname>
    <refpurpose>provision PostgreSQL and import SQLite databases</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>singine pg create database fromSQLite</command>
      <arg choice="req"><replaceable>SQLITE_DB</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><option>--db-name</option> <replaceable>NAME</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><option>--host-port</option> <replaceable>PORT</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><option>--user</option> <replaceable>USER</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><option>--password</option> <replaceable>PASSWORD</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><option>--replace</option></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      <command>singine pg</command> provides PostgreSQL workflows for Singine.
      Its primary operator path creates or reuses a local PostgreSQL Docker
      container, creates a target database, translates a SQLite schema into
      PostgreSQL DDL, and imports the data.
    </para>
    <para>
      This is the recommended way to move a local SQLite file such as
      <filename>/tmp/singine/sqlite.db</filename> into a network-reachable
      database endpoint suitable for JDBC clients.
    </para>
    <para>
      For callers running inside Docker Desktop Kubernetes, prefer the JDBC host
      <literal>host.docker.internal</literal> instead of
      <literal>127.0.0.1</literal>.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Workflow</title>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Choose the SQLite source database.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Run the import:
        </para>
        <programlisting language="bash">python3 -m singine.command pg create database fromSQLite /tmp/singine/sqlite.db</programlisting>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Note the printed JDBC URL and credentials.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          If you need a stable target name, rerun with
          <option>--db-name</option>.
        </para>
        <programlisting language="bash">python3 -m singine.command pg create database fromSQLite /tmp/singine/sqlite.db --db-name singine_bridge --replace</programlisting>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Defaults</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>container</term>
        <listitem><para><literal>singine-pg</literal></para></listitem>
